        My name is <span class="uk-text-success">Nikhil Dronamraju</span>.
        From a technical standpoint, I'm a dev with over 2 years of experience working with the tech shown
        below. My journey started off at Texas A&M University, where I was an industrial engineering major for 3 years. I ended up
        realizing that programming and building things was something I genuinely enjoyed doing, and eventually landed my first job as a dev.
        Since then, I've thrown myself into learning and building products!
        <br>
        <br>
        From a more personal standpoint, I'm a big reader. These days, some of my favorite reads have been
        <span class="uk-text-danger">Fight Club, Atomic Habits</span> and <span class="uk-text-danger">Man's Search for Meaning</span>.
        <br>
        <br>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/@landonstrong9161" target="_blank">I also make music!</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
